<subSubSection id="02D63443584850B956AFCF91DE2A3A9D" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="99CE6890D65D543A680E58D93702E388" pageNumber="15">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B2C692F08C4D6BB60FE4D7C1B58ADADE" pageNumber="15">An ophidiid genus with robust body; very small, overlapping scales on head and body; thick skin; posteriorly placed, enlarged kidneys; four lateral lines; dorsal fin origin above tip of pectorals; base of pelvic fin below hind margin of opercle; head broad with blunt snout; strong opercular spine covered by thick skin; upper jaw ends just behind eye; teeth granular, one median basibranchial tooth patch; anterior gill arch with 10-11 long rakers; number of rays in dorsal fin 80-89, caudal fin 8, anal fin 64-72, pelvic fin 2, pectoral fin 24-25; number of vertebrae 16-17 + 36 (in total 52-53).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AA496656610B499598C99593B18EB634" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="DD933DFE77FDC00913EAD7C7348B08C0" pageNumber="15">Similarity</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DE5FB7A5A28E8CB77C05E333EA94F515" pageNumber="15">
A phylogenetic analysis of the Ophidiidae needs to be made, but there are two genera, 
<taxonomicName id="87478BE7B69BA0C6C5625DD44C72E3C4" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:6467DD6E-CAFE-423C-B15C-7DF9F6BABE78" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Benthocometes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Benthocometes Goode &amp; Bean 1896:327" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Benthocometes (Goode and Bean, 1886)</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="199F75BD8294C64C23D60042DC135FDC" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:24013EF6-0125-478B-BEF7-CB33B201FEE1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Petrotyx" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Petrotyx Heller &amp; Snodgrass 1903:222" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Petrotyx Heller and Snodgrass, 1903</taxonomicName>
that are similar to 
<taxonomicName id="CDD83A215868C4260FC2C7C98C305A51" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Ventichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Ventichthys</taxonomicName>
in having a blunt snout, no free pectoral fin rays, granular teeth, and one basibranchial tooth patch. The differences between the three genera are shown in Table 2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7F6220D768336130D31E1A1DAC41554B" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="5D1A6F5963B3E7E4A7828BBDF1B03851" pageNumber="15">Etymology</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C735B6E8237A0B58AE3939F47755CE5F" pageNumber="15">Vent refers to the hydrothermal vent and ichthys to fish.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
